\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While it is impossible to predict the future, momentum has been created
 and some of the bottlenecks may be addressed sooner rather than later.
 For instance, a new processing facility is currently being constructed.
 It will be larger than any of the existing processing plants and it will
 specialize in infant formula which has high quality requirements.
 Pearl, as the largest processor, is slowly expanding its QBMPS.
 In a few months, it will be implemented in all MCCs that they own, and
 they will start expanding to cooperative MCCs.
 Amos, the second largest processor in the area, is also experimenting with
 its own QBMPS in some districts.
 Many experts believe that it is only a matter of time before quality-based
 payments become the norm.
 In fact, this may be one of the few virtues of the oligopsonistic market
 structure: once these large processors subscribe to the idea of quality
 based payments, all the others will have no other choice than to follow.
\end_layout

